Package neureka.devices

Interface Storage<V>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Device<V>, FileHandle<FinalType,​ValType>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractBaseDevice, AbstractDevice, CPU, CSVHandle, FileDevice, IDXHandle, OpenCLDevice
    public interface Storage<V>
    This is an abstract interface which simply describes "a thing that stores tensors". Therefore, the expected method signatures defining this abstract entity boil down to a "store" and a "restore" method. Classes like "OpenCLDevice" or "FileDevice" implement this interface indirectly (via the Device interface) because they are in essence also just entities that store tensors! Besides the "Device" interface this interface is also extended by the FileHandle interface which is an internal component of the FileDevice architecture...

    • Method Detail

      • store

        <T extends V> Storage<V> store​(Tsr<T> tensor)
        Implementations of this method ought to store the data of the tensor in whatever formant suites the underlying implementation and or final type. Classes like "OpenCLDevice" or "FileDevice" for example are tensor storages.
        Type Parameters:
        T - A valid data type of the tensor which should be stored on this device.
        Parameters:
        tensor - The tensor whose data ought to be stored.
        Returns:
        This Storage instance, to allow for method chaining.

        Returns:
